een dissolved the Galle administration, with the city presently administered by a commissioner. The main vision of the city is \"Building of moderate city through the supply of relatively increased utility services to the citizens who pay taxes to the Galle Municipal Council \". The other vision is to brand Galle as \"Green City-Green Galle\" to create and promote Galle as one of Sri Lanka's cool and healthy coastal cities with a clean green canopy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://greengalle.weebly.com/|title=Galle Green City - Make green city - Home|website=greengalle.weebly.com}}</ref>\n\n==Demographics==\nGalle is a sizeable city, by Sri Lankan standards, and has a population of 101,749 the majority of whom are of [[Sinhalese people|Sinhalese]] ethnicity. There is also a large population of [[Sri Lankan Moor]] particularly in the fort area, who descend from [[Arab]] merchants that settled in the ancient port of Galle. Galle is also notable for its foreign population, both residents and owners of holiday homes.\n{{bar box\n|title=Ethnicity in Galle (2012)\n|titlebar=#ddd\n|left1=Population\n|right1=Percent\n|float=right\n|bars=\n{{bar percent|[[Sinhalese people|Sinhalese]]|#FFFF00|67.00}}\n{{bar percent|[[Sri Lankan Moors|Muslims]]|#009000|30.20}}\n{{bar percent|[[Tamils]]|#FF8000|1.10}}\n{{bar percent|Others|#0080FF|0.20}}\n}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n|-\n!Ethnicity!!Population<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.statistics.gov.lk/PopHouSat/CPH2012Visualization/htdocs/index.php?usecase=indicator&action=DSMap&indId=10&district=Galle&Legend=3#|title=Population by Ethnicity according to D.S. Division and Sector: Galle District (Provisional)|year=2012|work=Census of Population Housing 2012|publisher=Department of Census and Statistics|url-status=dead|access-date=2019-08-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190301033246/http://www.statistics.gov.lk/PopHouSat/CPH2012Visualization/htdocs/index.php?usecase=indicator&action=DSMap&indId=10&district=Galle&Legend=3|archive-d